### insert() {#a52b05098bc5781643855cd42e1d5184c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::pair&lt; iterator, bool &gt; llvm::AAPointerInfo::RangeList::insert (<a href="#a6143879c6d6488c3d9b585efab710000">iterator</a> Pos, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="#a6175ccf7ad894a584b67faf0b0935546">RangeTy</a> &amp; R)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Insert <code>R</code> at the given iterator <code>Pos</code>, and merge if necessary.

This assumes that all ranges before <code>Pos</code> are LessThan <code>R</code>, and then maintains the sorted order for the suffix list.


<SectionUser title="Returns">
The place of insertion and true iff anything changed.
</SectionUser>
